==Paramètres individuels==
===Maximum no. competitors===
The maximum number of AI competitors. If you are playing a multiplayer game you may not want this too high otherwise other people may not be able to join and have their own company.

===Nb. de villes===
How many towns there will be in the game. This is also affected by the map size. A very small map will never get lots of towns, while a large map will a lot more.
This can be set in two places (here in difficulty settings or in the new terragenesis panel) when set to high you will have lots of towns and more passengers.

===Nb. d'industries===
How many industries there will be in the game. This is also affected by the map size. A very small map will never get lots of industries, while a large map will a lot more.
This can be found on the ''generate map dialog'' too.

===Emprunt initial maximum===
This is the maximum loan you can have at the start of the game. The amount slowly increases with game time.

===Taux d'intérêt initial===
This is the % of the loan you will be paying each game year. This doesn't pay off the loan itself.

===Coût d'entretien===
This is the cost per game year that all your vehicles have to pay. 

===Vitesse de développement des concurrents===
This is how fast the AI competitors build. If this is set too high they will have a giant network running in no time.

===Pannes de véhicules===
This is how often your vehicles breakdown.

===Multiplicateur de subventions===
How much the income is multiplied on a subsidy service.

===Coût des constructions===
This is how expensive it is for you to build anything and terraform the land.

===Type de terrain===
How the land is formed from flat to mountainous. This can be found on the ''generate map dialog'' too.

===Quantité de mer/lacs===
This is how much of the map is taken up by the water. This can be found on the ''generate map dialog'' too.

===Économie===
L'économie ne peut entrer en [[fr/Manual/Économie#recession|récession]] si l'option sélectionnée est "Stable".

===Demi-tour des trains===
Détermine dans quels cas les trains peuvent faire demi-tour. Ne change pas la possibilité pour le joueur, même si l'option "À la fin des lignes seulement" est choisie, de cliquer sur le bouton "demi-tour" dans l'interface de contrôle des trains.

===Désastres===
Active ou désactive les [[fr/Manual/Catastrophes|catastrophes]].

===Attitude des mairies face aux aménagements===
Gouverne la façon dont les municipalités voient les travaux que vous voulez effectuer dans leur ville.

